<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 07 at 7:30PM MDT until further notice by NWS RapidCity</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 745 PM MDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN HAAKON COUNTY...
At 730 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 3 miles southwest of
Grindstone Butte, or 13 miles northwest of Philip, moving east at 25
mph.
HAZARD...Half dollar size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Grindstone and Grindstone Butte.
HAIL THREAT...OBSERVED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.25 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
